Absolutely the funniest book about Vietnam is a book called Cannon Fodder.  It was recently reviewed over a 4 month period on the newsgroup alt.war.vietnam.<br><br>
What makes it so funny is that the author is serious about such things as Vietnam being a heavily industrialized nation, about APCs having pneumatic tires instead of tracks, of hand grenades being able to blow upbuildings.<br><br>
The author even claims to have had a brown bear as a pet in Bien Hoa (no brown bears in SEA).<br><br>
A review of it can be found on http://www.olywa.net/sdotctho/waste/cfsrsum.html<br><br>
The guys and gals on alt.war.vietnam will be happy to answer questions . .<br><br>
The consensus there is that the author never actually served in Vietnam
